<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="62" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1166,1912]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,292,1166,1192]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Distribution:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Gall" authorityYear="1852" box="[320,590,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusangula">
<emphasis box="[320,590,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Callitriche obtusangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from Europe and North Africa. It occurs from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1314,1354,1167,1193]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">UK</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry name="Netherlands" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">the Netherlands</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[305,387,1202,1228]" name="Austria" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Austria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[441,520,1202,1228]" name="Greece" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Greece</collectingCountry>
in the east, as well as in 
<collectingCountry box="[796,900,1203,1229]" name="Morocco" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[909,996,1202,1228]" name="Algeria" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1053,1140,1202,1228]" name="Tunisia" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
. It is at the southern limit of its range in 
<collectingCountry box="[267,371,1239,1265]" name="Morocco" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, where it has been recorded from three sites in the north and on the Central Plateau (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1408,1238,1264]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1976,1998]" captionTargetBox="[157,1429,191,1951]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[151,1435,190,1951]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. Known distribution of Callitriche species in Morocco. A. C. obtusangula. B. C. regis-jubae. C. C. stagnalis. D. C. truncata subsp. occidentalis. E. C. truncata subsp. truncata. F. All records of all Callitriche species in Morocco." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6875725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6875725/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1166,1912]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,445,1274,1300]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Habitat and ecology:</emphasis>
—Throughout most of its range, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Gall" authorityYear="1852" box="[829,1099,1274,1300]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusangula">
<emphasis box="[829,1099,1274,1300]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Callitriche obtusangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
typically occurs in permanent waterbodies such as rivers, fen drains, ditches, and pools in freshwater systems, extending into the upper margins of brackish coastal wetlands. In 
<collectingCountry box="[464,565,1347,1373]" name="Morocco" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Morocco</collectingCountry>
it has been recorded from a stream, a reservoir, and low-lying wet grassland. At one site in a stream near Oulmès, it was recorded with a range of species of which 39% can be considered truly aquatic, 48% marginal, and 13% terrestrial, reflecting the perennial nature of the stream. Other species recorded were similar to those with which it occurs in Europe, including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[711,941,1454,1480]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis box="[711,941,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Callitriche stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="von Linne (1753: 992)" authorityName="von Linne" authorityPageNumber="992" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ceratophyllaceae" genus="Ceratophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ceratophyllales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="demersum">
<emphasis box="[956,1247,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Ceratophyllum demersum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="von Linne, C." pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="ref17941" refString="von Linne, C. (1753) Species Plantarum. Laurentius Salvius, Stockholm, 1200 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 669" type="book" year="1753">von Linné (1753: 992)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(von Linne 1753: 251) Koch (1824: 126)" authorityName="Koch" authorityPageNumber="126" authorityYear="1824" baseAuthorityName="von Linne" baseAuthorityPageNumber="251" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[201,956,1490,1517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Helosciadium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nodiflorum">
<emphasis box="[201,488,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Helosciadium nodiflorum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="von Linne, C." box="[503,739,1490,1517]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="ref17941" refString="von Linne, C. (1753) Species Plantarum. Laurentius Salvius, Stockholm, 1200 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 669" type="book" year="1753">von Linné 1753: 251</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Koch, W. D. J." box="[754,956,1490,1516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" pagination="55 - 156" refId="ref15359" refString="Koch, W. D. J. (1824) Generum Tribuumque Plantarum Umbelliferarum Nova Dispositio. Nova Acta Physico-Medica Academiae Caesareae Leopoldino-Carolinae Naturae Curiosorum 12: 55 - 156. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 113876  page / 107 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1824">Koch (1824: 126)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Linne" authorityYear="1753" box="[967,1114,1490,1516]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Lemna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gibba">
<emphasis box="[967,1114,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Lemna gibba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webb" authorityYear="1967" box="[1128,1311,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lythraceae" genus="Lythrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="portula">
<emphasis box="[1128,1311,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Lythrum portula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="1812" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Nasturtium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="officinale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Nasturtium officinale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Poiret (1816: 535)" authorityName="Poiret" authorityPageNumber="535" authorityYear="1816" box="[258,730,1526,1553]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Haloragaceae" genus="Potamogeton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nodosus">
<emphasis box="[258,509,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Potamogeton nodosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Poiret, J. L. M." box="[518,730,1526,1553]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="ref16115" refString="Poiret, J. L. M. (1816) Encyclopedie methodique. Botanique. Supplement, Tome 4. Agasse, Paris, 731 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 826" type="book" year="1816">Poiret (1816: 535)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="von Linne (1753: 620)" authorityName="von Linne" authorityPageNumber="620" authorityYear="1753" box="[745,1289,1526,1553]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Scrophulariaceae" genus="Scrophularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="auriculata">
<emphasis box="[745,1018,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Scrophularia auriculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="von Linne, C." box="[1027,1289,1526,1553]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" refId="ref17941" refString="von Linne, C. (1753) Species Plantarum. Laurentius Salvius, Stockholm, 1200 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 669" type="book" year="1753">von Linné (1753: 620)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pennell" authorityYear="1921" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Veronica" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="catenata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Veronica catenata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is a lowland species in the north of its range (Lansdown 2007), but has been recorded up to 
<quantity box="[1334,1421,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200 m</quantity>
in Sicily. Elevation in 
<collectingCountry box="[357,463,1599,1625]" name="Morocco" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Morocco</collectingCountry>
: 
<quantity box="[473,601,1598,1625]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" unit="m" value="550.0" valueMax="1100.0" valueMin="0.0">0—1100 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1166,1912]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,342,1634,1660]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Recognition:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Gall" authorityYear="1852" box="[370,639,1634,1660]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusangula">
<emphasis box="[370,639,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Callitriche obtusangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[1066,1279,1634,1660]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis box="[1066,1187,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Callitriche</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[136,237,1671,1697]" name="Morocco" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Morocco</collectingCountry>
by the combination of large, unwinged fruit with parallel mericarps, and large anthers with yellow pollen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1166,1912]" box="[189,902,1706,1733]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,345,1706,1732]" pageId="9" pageNumber="62">Illustrations:</emphasis>
